"{\n    \"Title\": \"BISHOP'S UNIVERSITYNotes to Financial Statements (continued)\",\n    \"row 1\": \"Year ended April 30, 2018\",\n    \"row 2\": \"2. Significant accounting policies (continued):\",\n    \"row 3\": \"(i) Tangible capital assets (continued):\",\n    \"row 4\": \"Tangible capital assets of ancillary enterprises are added to the Capital Fund and the payments on the related long-term debt or the contribution to financing\",\n    \"row 5\": \"for acquisitions are presented as an Interfund transfer in the statement of changes in fund balances.\",\n    \"row 6\": \"Amortization:\",\n    \"row 7\": \"The annual amortization rates and periods are prescribed by the MEES. Amortization is based on their estimated useful lives according to the straight-line\",\n    \"row 8\": \"method over the following periods:\",\n    \"row 9\": \"Asset Period\",\n    \"row 10\": \"Land improvements 10 or 20 years\",\n    \"row 11\": \"Buildings 20, 40 or 50 years\",\n    \"row 12\": \"Building renovations 25, 30 or 40 years\",\n    \"row 13\": \"Furnishings, rolling equipment, software 5 years\",\n    \"row 14\": \"Equipment 5, 10 of 15 years\",\n    \"row 15\": \"Computer hardware 3 years\",\n    \"row 16\": \"Library collection 10 years\",\n    \"row 17\": \"When the University recognizes that a tangible capital asset no longer has any long-term service potential, the excess of net carrying amount of the tangible\",\n    \"row 18\": \"capital asset over its residual value is recognized as an expense in the statement of operations\",\n    \"row 19\": \"(j) Other assets:\",\n    \"row 20\": \"The University holds an interest, representing 1/19th of the cost of a high speed telecommunication system pursuant to an agreement between the MEES, the\",\n    \"row 21\": \"R\\u00e9seau interordinateurs scientifique Qu\\u00e9b\\u00e9cois (RISQ) Inc. and the universities. The annual amertization is established using the straight-line method over\",\n    \"row 22\": \"the term of the contract signed by the MEES and the University (16 years).\",\n    \"row 23\": \"(k) Servicing of long-term debt:\",\n    \"row 24\": \"For the long-term debt obligations, the Government of Qu\\u00e9bec funds annual principal and interest payment requirements on behalf of the University, which are\",\n    \"row 25\": \"recorded as decreases in the related debt.\",\n    \"row 26\": \"3. Interest expenses:\",\n    \"row 27\": \"2018 2017\",\n    \"row 28\": \"Interest on long-term debt $ 913,111 $ 866,672\",\n    \"row 29\": \"Interest on bank indebtedness, credit facility and banker's acceptances 598,264 652,861\",\n    \"row 30\": \"$ 1,511,375 $ 1,519,533\",\n    \"row 31\": \"4. Interfund transfers:\",\n    \"row 32\": \"During the year, the University transferred $2,836,095 (2017 - $2,003,865) from the Operating Fund to the Capital Fund in order to finance net cash disbursements\",\n    \"row 33\": \"related to fixed assets, long-term debt repayments and payments of interest on long-term debt, and transferred $2,695,000 (2017 - $4,968,000) from the Operating\",\n    \"row 34\": \"Fund to the Capital Fund as a reserve mainly for future assets acquisitions and renovations\",\n    \"row 35\": \"5. Government assistance:\",\n    \"row 36\": \"The MEES financially supports certain capital projects of the University each year for which the form of funding is finalized at a later date. Included in the interfund\",\n    \"row 37\": \"amounts due to and from the Operating and Capital Funds respectively is approximately $8,308,590 (2017 - $9,422,497) of capital expenditures and interest on\",\n    \"row 38\": \"temporary financing incurred as at year-end and for which the funding has yet to be either received or finalized by the MEES.\",\n    \"row 39\": \"6. Investments:\",\n    \"row 40\": \"2018 2017\",\n    \"row 41\": \"Balanced fund, McLean Budden, representing charitable annuity donation fund $ - $ 984,346\",\n    \"row 42\": \"Money Market Fund, McLean Budden, repr